Took CS170, CS70, and EE16B together last semester. It is definitely manageable (and I still had a lot of free time at the second half of semester). End up with A s in all three classes. I was a freshman if that makes a difference.

--------------------------

Just offering a second opinion: CS 70 is a lot of workload, even if you do the test-only option (because you still need to keep up with the material), and I would never have been able to take 3 techs along with CS 70. I haven't taken CS 170, but it sounds like CS 70 and CS 170 would be too much of a workload for me personally. I have seen other people take CS 70 with EE 16B however.

children.subject: I think if you understood/remember the linear algebra part in 16a and you feel comfortable with it then switching out 16b for 54 should make things easier! The concepts in 54 will be more in-depth but having that 16a knowledge will definitely help. It would probably be best to take 54 when the material is still somewhat fresh as well!
